From: Nickel Browser Team <team@nickel-browser.org>
Date: Thu, 01 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 08/10] nickel: tor-integration — Tor private-tab controller

Add Tor private-tab support.  Opening a "New Tor Tab" starts a Tor
daemon subprocess (bundled in the app directory) and routes all traffic
for that tab through the SOCKS5 proxy on localhost:9150.

Architecture:
  NickelTorController    — spawns/monitors the tor daemon, manages lifecycle
  NickelTorTabHelper     — per-WebContents helper; reroutes requests via
                            the Tor SOCKS5 proxy when a tab is in Tor mode

The Tor binary itself is NOT included in this patch; it must be downloaded
separately and placed in the app directory (see docs/BUILD.md for the
bundling instructions).

Security notes:
  - DNS lookups for Tor tabs are also routed through the proxy (no DNS leak)
  - WebRTC is disabled for all Tor tabs unconditionally
  - javascript: navigations that would open non-Tor URLs are blocked
